On the 21st anniversary of the genocide in Rwanda, President Obama issued a statement to commemorate the lives lost and honor those who risked their lives to save others. He emphasized the importance of standing together to prevent mass atrocities and reaffirmed the commitment to bring justice to those responsible for the tragedy. The President also acknowledged the progress made by the people of Rwanda in healing and lifting people out of poverty, and promised continued support from the United States in preventing such atrocities and promoting peace.